---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Psychiatric Rehabilitation (PRP) - The WEL Foundation">
  <div class="container" style="padding: var(--spacing-8) 0;">
    <header class="reveal-on-scroll" style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-8); text-align:center; max-width: 800px; margin-inline: auto;">
      <div style="font-size: 3rem; margin-bottom: var(--spacing-3);">🧠</div>
      <h1 style="font-size: 3rem; color: var(--color-primary-blue); margin-bottom: var(--spacing-3);">Psychiatric Rehabilitation Program (PRP)</h1>
      <p style="font-size: 1.15rem; color: var(--color-text-muted); line-height: 1.6;">
        Therapy provides the mental blueprint, but PRP provides the mortar and bricks. Our Psychiatric Rehabilitation Program bridges the gap between clinical insight and the rigorous demands of daily community living.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="grid" style="grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(350px, 1fr)); gap: var(--spacing-6); margin-bottom: var(--spacing-8);">
      <article class="card reveal-on-scroll stagger-1">
        <h2 style="font-size: 1.5rem; color: var(--color-primary-light-blue);">Adult PRP Services</h2>
        <p style="color: var(--color-text-main); line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: var(--spacing-3);">
          For adults struggling to maintain sovereignty due to severe psychological distress (e.g., Schizophrenia, Severe Depression, or Bipolar Disorder), our rehabilitation coordinators act as active community allies.
        </p>
        <ul style="color: var(--color-text-muted); padding-left: var(--spacing-4); line-height: 1.6;">
          <li>Assistance with entitlement programs (housing, SNAP, SSI/SSDI)</li>
          <li>Financial literacy and monthly budgeting skills</li>
          <li>Hygiene, home-maintenance, and nutritional coaching</li>
          <li>Medical appointment coordination and medication management support</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="card reveal-on-scroll stagger-2">
        <h2 style="font-size: 1.5rem; color: var(--color-primary-light-blue);">Child & Adolescent PRP</h2>
        <p style="color: var(--color-text-main); line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: var(--spacing-3);">
          Children facing behavioral disruptions or emotional dysregulation require targeted intervention to prevent adverse lifelong trajectories. We work directly in the home, community, and school settings.
        </p>
        <ul style="color: var(--color-text-muted); padding-left: var(--spacing-4); line-height: 1.6;">
          <li>Anger management and conflict resolution strategies</li>
          <li>IEP (Individualized Education Program) advocacy and school interfacing</li>
          <li>Prosocial boundary setting and peer-relationship coaching</li>
          <li>Family-system strengthening and parental support strategies</li>
        </ul>
      </article>
    </div>

    <section class="reveal-on-scroll" style="text-align: center; max-width: 700px; margin-inline: auto;">
      <h2 style="font-size: 2rem; color: var(--color-primary-blue); margin-bottom: var(--spacing-3);">How does PRP differ from Therapy?</h2>
      <p style="font-size: 1.1rem; color: var(--color-text-muted); line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: var(--spacing-5);">
        While traditional therapy happens within the confines of an office and focuses on internal emotional processing, <strong>PRP is hyper-practical and occurs in the real world</strong>. If therapy teaches a client why they get anxious at the grocery store, a PRP coordinator will literally walk alongside the client through the grocery store to practice grounding techniques in real-time.
      </p>
      
      <div style="background-color: var(--color-bg-offset); padding: var(--spacing-4); border-radius: var(--radius-sm); border: 1px solid var(--color-border); text-align: left;">
        <h4 style="color: var(--color-primary-blue); margin-bottom: var(--spacing-1);">Eligibility Criteria:</h4>
        <p style="color: var(--color-text-muted); font-size: 0.95rem;">Clients must be concurrently enrolled in an outpatient mental health therapy program and meet priority population diagnosis criteria established by the State of Maryland.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

  </div>
</Layout>
